                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a01">
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                      <locus target="#7r"/>, lower margin (in pen): Prayer from the original owner, “O, God of David, keep your servant Gäbrä Mäsqäl,” and a list of baptismal names
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a02">
                      <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                      <locus target="#150v"/>: note of ownership, in later hand, in ink pen
                      </desc>
                      </item>

                      <item xml:id="e01">
                      <desc>
                        Headband and tailband are made from strips of leather painted red
                        and black. This work also has several other features (leather bound
                        cover, large proportions, fine and uniform parchment, the trim of the
                        text block, ornate quire numbers, the finishing of the turn-ins, etc.)
                        which indicate that it may have been produced in the Government
                        scriptorium. However, the work is not of the very finest quality
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e02">
                      <desc>
                      Psalm 118 contains the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e03">
                      <desc>
                      Numbered quires: quires 2–15
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e04">
                      <desc>
                        Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#39v"/>);
                        and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#34r"/>);
                        erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#149r"/>);
                        text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#35r #42r #85v"/>).
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e05">
                      <desc>
                        The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line.
                        Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an
                        appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate
                        script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe
                        completes the line of text above or below the end of the line
                        (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of
                        lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., <locus target="#2r #2v #3r #4r"/>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>

                    </list>
                  </additions>
